  "prompt": "Why doesn't Wetransfer give the shared file links immediately on the screen after the upload completes, like SendSpace does?",
  "response": "WeTransfer and SendSpace have different approaches to user experience and file sharing, which can explain the differences in how they handle link generation after an upload. Here are a few reasons why WeTransfer might not provide shared file links immediately on the screen:\n\n1. **User Experience Design**: WeTransfer focuses on a clean and minimalist interface. Their design may prioritize a seamless, distraction-free experience over immediately displaying links. Instead, they send the link via email to ensure users have a reliable backup and can easily share it later.\n\n2. **File Processing**: After the upload completes, WeTransfer may take a moment to process the file, create the link, and ensure everything is in order before presenting the link. This processing time may not align with their user experience goals of immediate feedback.\n\n3. **Link Management**: By sending the link via email, WeTransfer can help users manage files better, as they can easily refer back to the email for future access or share it with others directly from their inbox.\n\n4. **Security Considerations**: WeTransfer may have security measures in place that dictate how and when share links are generated. By using email, users are less likely to forget or lose track of their files.\n\n5. **Branding and Marketing**: Sending links via email can also be a part of WeTransfer's branding strategy, encouraging users to engage with the platform through their email notifications.\n\nEach service has its strengths, and users may prefer one over the other based on their specific needs and preferences.",
